      "message": "I’m not so sure, to be honest. But I do agree this method is rather busy. How about a middle ground? Since I’m not using any keys, I don’t need to use entrySet, and Objects.requireNonNull doesn’t need to be used inline.\n\n```\nprivate boolean tapiServiceExists(\n        String openRoadmServiceName,\n        Map\u003cConnectivityServiceKey, ConnectivityService\u003e\n                connectivityServices) {\n\n    for (ConnectivityService service\n            : connectivityServices.values()) {\n\n        Map\u003cNameKey, Name\u003e names \u003d service.getName();\n        if (names \u003d\u003d null) {\n            continue;\n        }\n\n        for (Name nme : names.values()) {\n            if (serviceNameEqualsTapiServiceName(\n                    openRoadmServiceName, nme)) {\n\n                LOG.info(\"Service {} already exists in TAPI\",\n                        openRoadmServiceName);\n\n                return true;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    return false;\n}\n```\n\nI suggest adding this change as a follow-up to avoid having to restart all the integration tests: https://git.opendaylight.org/gerrit/c/transportpce/+/121863",
